            {
                "s2_paper_id": "0239bc1c9d96332017047f94e275e23c62531483",
                "title": "Exploring F/CF3 substituted oxocarbenium ions for the diastereoselective assembly of highly substituted tetrahydrofurans.",
                "year": 2023,
                "venue": "Chemical Communications",
                "citation_count": 0,
                "reference_count": 0,
                "abstract": "Understanding the influence of emerging fluorinated motifs is of a crucial importance in the context of the exponentially growing exploitation of fluorine in many fields. Herein, we report on the dramatic effect of a local partial charge inversion by replacing a CHCH3 group by a CFCF3. This strategy allows the diastereoselective reduction of 5-membered ring oxocarbenium ions to access highly substituted tetrahydrofurans.",
